1 olive oil
3 clove garlic
20 g butter
1 packet basmati rice
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet chicken thigh
2 tsp honey
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 bag parsley
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1.5 cup water
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Middle Eastern Seasoning

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a
drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Cook 1/2
the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add basmati rice, the water and vegetable
stock powder, stir, then bring to the boil.
• Reduce the heat to low and cover with a lid.
Cook for 10 minutes, then remove from the heat
and keep covered until rice is tender and water is
absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so
don't peek!

• While the rice is cooking, in a medium frying
pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high
heat. Cook the remaining garlic until fragrant,
1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl, then add
Greek-style yoghurt and stir to combine.
Season to taste.

• In a medium bowl, combine chicken thigh,
Middle Eastern seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil
and a pinch of salt.
• Return the frying pan to medium heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken, turning
occasionally, until golden and cooked through,
14-16 minutes (depending on the size).
• Remove pan from heat and add the honey,
turning chicken to coat.

• While the chicken is cooking, finely chop tomato
and cucumber.

• In a second medium bowl, combine a drizzle of
white wine vinegar and olive oil and a pinch of
salt and pepper.
• Add cucumber and tomato and mix to combine.

• Slice spiced chicken. Divide garlic rice between
bowls and top with Middle Eastern chicken and
cucumber salsa.
• Drizzle over garlic yoghurt and tear over parsley
to serve. Enjoy!